description:
secretx-core/src/lib.rs:984-989, 1007-1012: every backend that produces a Backend or Unavailable error writes:

    SecretError::Backend {
        backend: "my-backend",
        source: e.into(),
    }

This is repeated dozens of times across the 18 backend crates. Idiomatic Rust would expose constructors:

    impl SecretError {
        pub fn backend(name: &'static str, e: impl Into<Box<dyn Error + Send + Sync>>) -> Self {
            SecretError::Backend { backend: name, source: e.into() }
        }
        pub fn unavailable(name: &'static str, e: impl Into<Box<dyn Error + Send + Sync>>) -> Self {
            SecretError::Unavailable { backend: name, source: e.into() }
        }
    }

Then 'Err(SecretError::backend("my-backend", e))' is the single-line form that 18 backends all share. This pairs well with avkc.5 — change name to Cow<'static, str> and the same constructor handles both literal and owned cases.

P2 because it's a polish improvement; the existing struct-literal form works.
